message: Focus on using the 'filter' tool. To achieve 100 points, first use 'filter' on a mundane liquid ingredient (e.g., 'morning dew', 'tree sap', 'honey nectar') to get a 'filtered mundane liquid' (30 points). Then, use 'filter' on a magical ingredient that can become a liquid (e.g., 'volcanic fumes', 'dragon's breath', 'ghostly vapor', 'kraken ink', 'whispering wind') to get a 'filtered magical liquid' (30 points). Finally, combine these two filtered liquids to consistently create a 100-point item. The 'vial' tool was only useful with 'sunstone' for a 30-point item, but filtering worked more broadly for magical components. Avoid using 'vial' on magical gases as it resulted in negative points.

message: Focus on making 30-point items first. Use 'vial' on 'solid, mundane' ingredients (like frog leg, bat wing, rose petal, dandelion, amber) to get 'liquid, extracted, mundane'. Also use 'vial' on 'solid, magical' ingredients (like unicorn horn, dragon scale, mandrake root, sunstone) to get 'liquid, extracted, magical'. Use 'filter' on 'liquid, magical' (like basilisk venom) or 'gas, magical' (like whispering wind, ghostly vapor) to get 'liquid, filtered, magical'. The best strategy for 100 points is to combine a 'liquid, extracted, mundane' item with a 'liquid, extracted, magical' item. For example, combine 'frog leg extract' (liquid, extracted, mundane) with 'dragon scale extract' (liquid, extracted, magical). Avoid applying tools to items that are already processed or have negative value, as this usually makes things worse. Good luck!

message: Focus on creating 30-point items by using tools on single ingredients. Vial on any solid ingredient (mundane or magical) gives 30 points (extracted, liquid). Filter on any gas ingredient (mundane or magical) gives 30 points (filtered, liquid). Filter on mundane liquid also gives 30 points. Once you have two 30-point items, combine them IF they are both 'mundane' or both 'magical' AND both 'extracted' or both 'filtered'. This will yield a 60-point item. Do NOT combine more than two ingredients, and do NOT mix mundane and magical items in a combination, as this almost always drastically lowers the value. Once you reach 60 points, submit immediately; attempts to combine further generally result in negative scores.

Avoid using tools on liquids or gases, and generally avoid mixing ingredients until you have these two specific types of 30-point extracts.

To get 60 points, combine *two* processed ingredients of the *same type* (e.g., two magical liquid extracts, or two mundane liquid extracts). Avoid mixing magical and mundane items, and do not combine three or more processed items, as this drastically reduces value, often below 30 points or even negative. Re-processing an already extracted or filtered item with another tool is generally ineffective or detrimental.
